
# Word Frequency Histogram

This project is a React frontend application that fetches the contents of a text file, calculates the frequency of occurrence of each word, and displays a histogram of the 20 most occurring words. It also provides an option to export the histogram data as a CSV file.

## Components

The application consists of the following components:

- `App`: The main component that handles the fetching of data, calculates word frequencies, and renders the histogram and export functionality.

## Libraries and Plugins Used

The project utilizes the following libraries and plugins:

- React: A JavaScript library for building user interfaces.
- react-chartjs-2: A React wrapper for Chart.js, which provides interactive and customizable charts.
- Chart.js: A JavaScript library for creating charts.

## Usage

To run the application locally, follow these steps:

1. Clone the repository or download the source code.
2. Install the dependencies by running `npm install`.
3. Start the development server by running `npm start`.
4. Open your browser and visit `http://localhost:3000` to view the application.
5. Click the "Submit" button to fetch the text file and generate the word frequency histogram.
6. The histogram chart will be displayed, showing the top 20 words with the highest occurrence.
7. Click the "Export" button to download the histogram data as a CSV file.

## Deploy

Deployed this project on netlify with following steps:

1. Run build command on terminal `npm run build`.
2. Dist folder is created.
3. Upload this folder on netlify and then generated a link.

## Deployment link - https://word-frequency20.netlify.app/